metadata.title: Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil
aws::graph::propositions: On 8 August 2009, a Piper PA-32R collided with an Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil over the Hudson River.
Both aircraft crashed into the Hudson River after the collision.
There were no survivors from the 8 August 2009 Hudson River collision.
On 10 June 2012, an Eurocopter AS350 B3e belonging to the Kenya Police Air Wing crashed in Kibiku area in Ngong Forest.
Ngong Forest is located west of Nairobi, Kenya.
The 10 June 2012 Kenya crash killed at least six people.
Kenya's Interior Security Minister George Saitoti was killed in the 10 June 2012 crash.
George Saitoti's deputy Orwa Ojode was killed in the 10 June 2012 crash.
On March 30, 2013, an Alaska State Troopers Eurocopter AS350 B3 with registration N911AA crashed.
The Alaska State Troopers helicopter impacted terrain while maneuvering during a search and rescue flight.
The Alaska State Troopers helicopter crash occurred near Talkeetna, Alaska.
All three people onboard the Alaska State Troopers helicopter died.
On 7 June 2014, a Helibrás HB-350BA crashed after takeoff in Aruanã, Goiás state, Brazil.
Helibrás HB-350BA is a variant of the Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil manufactured in Brazil.
All people on board the Helibrás HB-350BA died in the 7 June 2014 crash.
Retired football player Fernandão was among those killed in the 7 June 2014 crash.

text:
On 8 August 2009, a Piper PA-32R collided with an AS350 over the Hudson River, with both aircraft crashing into the Hudson River. There were no survivors.
On 10 June 2012, an AS350 B3e belonging to the Kenya Police Air Wing crashed in Kibiku area in Ngong Forest, west of Nairobi, Kenya, killing at least six people, including Kenya's Interior Security Minister George Saitoti and his deputy Orwa Ojode.
On March 30, 2013, an Alaska State Troopers AS350 B3 N911AA impacted terrain while maneuvering during a search and rescue flight near Talkeetna, Alaska. All three onboard died.
On 7 June 2014, a Helibrás HB-350BA crashed after takeoff, in Aruanã, Goiás state, Brazil. All on board died, including retired football player Fernandão.
